summary: The Original Captain Marvel (aka Shazam) comics finished there run in 1953 (65 years ago) and was re introduced with DC in 1972...
body:
The Original Captain Marvel (aka Shazam) comics finished there run in 1953 (65 years ago) and was re introduced with DC in 1972 (46 years ago) under the name Shazam due to Marvel Comics having the the rights to the Name ‘Captain Marvel’ when they introduced their Captain Mar’Vell in 1967 (51 years ago, 14 years after the Original one ended).


So why do people still call Shazam Captain Marvel? His name change happened years ago yet people continue to use it for him. It’s not like anyone here grew up with Shazam as Captain Marvel, unless you around 65 years old.

summary: Since Captain Marvel is in the public eye again; I might as well show these first two pages of the character’s first appearance....
caption:
Since Captain Marvel is in the public eye again; I might as well show these first two pages of the character’s first appearance.

Because I really; really like them, and the sense of wonder and mystery they evoke, just the sheer atmosphere, awe and sense of genuine wonder that I feel makes superhero comics great.

Also, as per usual, friendly reminder that the comic this comes from (Whiz Comics #2) is public domain. And, therefore, via the US’ copyright laws that if a character’s first appearance is PD they are PD, Captain Marvel is almost definitely in the public domain.

Ditto with pretty much all of the elements of Captain Marvel except for Black Adam (Who is very much copyrighted), but including Doctor Siviana, Mary Marvel, Tawky Tawny, and even the amazing Mr. Mind.

Though, again; they are still trademarked; so you’d probably have to be very careful in how you use ‘em…
